'''Characters''' are what the player can control to move around in a [[stage]]. Each character starts with its own unique [[weapon|weapon(s)]] and passive bonus.

There are currently 207 official playable characters. The base game has 54 characters, 22 can be obtained by discovering [[Secrets|secrets]]. The DLCs have a combined roster of 153 characters, 56 of them being secret ones. All non-secret characters need to be purchased using [[Gold Coin (currency)|gold]], increased by 10% additively per characters purchased, with the exception of [[Antonio]], being the first basic character a new player uses; [[Queen Sigma]], who requires an achievement but costs 0 [[Gold Coin (currency)|gold]] to purchase; and [[Dracula]], who is immediately unlocked upon obtaining the [[Black Disk]] and does not require a purchase. Some of these characters require an achievement to unlock for purchase. Certain characters have alternate unlocking method unlisted.    

Certain characters are duo, which means a secondary character will follow the main character. Both characters get their leveling up by turns, and shares the same '''upgrade pool''' (which means if both of them takes the same weapon or passive item, both of them will not be able to [[Evolution|evolve]] it). Passive items can be shared between both of them for evolution. [[Stage item|Stage items]] will only be added to the main character's inventory. Secondary character will not take damage normally.    

[[File:Difference between bought, unlocked, and locked characters.png|thumb|Here, {{slink|Antonio Belpaese|txt=Antonio}} is bought, {{slink|Arca Ladonna|txt=Arca}} is locked, and {{slink|Suor Clerici|txt=Clerici}} is unlocked but not bought.]]
The unlock conditions for each character can be found in the [[Unlocks]] menu. It should be noted that if a new player unlocks at least one new character, the character selection menu will start to show silhouettes of other locked characters, instead of just showing the character select icons of {{slink|Antonio Belpaese}}, {{slink|Imelda Belpaese}}, {{slink|Pasqualina Belpaese}}, and {{slink|Gennaro Belpaese}}.
*Characters that are unlocked and bought will have a gray selection icon shown with their character and starting weapon, with their name marked in white;
*Characters that are unlocked but not bought will also have a gray selection icon and their starting weapon shown, but the characters themselves will have a black silhouette and their name is marked in gray;
*Characters that are locked have their selection icon entirely colored blue-gray, with the character silhouette, character name, and starting weapon being translucent.

